title: Double differential neutron emission cross sections of Pb,Cu and Al for 14.6 MeV neutrons

x4codes.shortRef: Prog: Pakistan report to the I.N.D.C., No.006 (1986)

x4freetext: IAEA contract 3310/RB
Double differential neutron emission cross sections
of Pb,Cu and Al for 14.6 MeV neutrons
T(d,n)4He using 120 keV deuterons
Natural targets each of 5.1 cm diameter and 5.1 cm
long were used
Energies of emitted neutrons were measured
by TOF technique,the angular distributions were
normalized with respect to a long counter
NE213 liquid scintillator 12.7x12.7 cm was used
The cross sections of the ground and first excited
states of C-12 were used for the neutron emission
cross section determination

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Science and Engineering, Vol.65, p.331 (1978)

x4freetext: Data from INDC(PAK)-6, 1986
For the double-differential cross sections (subentries
2-18), authors state that data are in C.M. system but
angles given are in lab system
Flux normalization -3%
Inscattering -      4%
Neutron detector efficiency - 5%
Cross section normalization - 6%
Statistical error
by VG
SD:Updated to new date formats,lower case.
COMMON section and codes for uncertainties were
added in Subent 001. Col. DATA-ERR in Subents 002-018
was multiplied by 100 to convert uncertainty in %.
OS. Changed headings to E-CM and DATA-CM in subentries
with double-diff. data.

x4freetext: Angle integrated data
for different energy bins
Compiler`s comment:
Authors use units mb/MeV in the table, which makes no
difference for these data because there are 1 MeV bins.
They have however one point for a 6 - 11 MeV bin
summing up 5 bins of 1 MeV each. Therefore we use
units mb for this table for internal consistency.
Author`s units for the 6-11 MeV bin are, strictly
speaking, inconsistent with the rest of their table.
Compare also Table 1 of the reference (compiled in
subentry 19) which has the same type of data for Pb
and gives units mb.
Data from Table 2 of reference
Point data see 30709023

COMMENT, REACTION modified accordingly.
